  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations. These typically include:\n\n1. Reporting requirements for financial institutions\n2. Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n3. Mandatory transaction reporting\n4. Penalties for non-compliance\n5. Requirements to identify and report suspicious activities\n\nIn the United States, key laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. Most developed countries have similar comprehensive AML legal frameworks.",
